@NODE Introduction
@Next Main


   ------------
   Tupelo Fonts
   ------------

   Tupelo fonts are fixed sized fonts that can be used as a replacement
   to the system default topaz font. It will display 90+ characters
   across a standard size screen.


   If you use these fonts, send me a postcard:

                             David W. Ferguson
                             Route 8 Box 87
                             Pontotoc, Mississippi  38863
                             United States of America


   Copyright ©1994 David W. Ferguson, fully distributable.



@ENDNODE

@NODE Installation
@Next Main


  ----------------------
  Installation of Fonts:
  ----------------------


  @{"Using the Installer " link Installer}

  @{"Manual Installation " link Manual}



@ENDNODE

@NODE Installer
@Next Installation


   Installing fonts using the Installer:


   Just double-click on the "DWFfont_Install" icon and the Installer
   program will copy all the files over to your Fonts: directory.



   Installer© 1991-1993 Commodore-Amiga,Inc.

@ENDNODE

@NODE Manual
@Next Installation


   Installing fonts using AmigaDOS:

   From the Shell, type the following command.

      Copy DF0:Fonts to Fonts: all

@ENDNODE

